## Limitations

- **Limited data:** {{ history_days }} days of usable history since
  {{ data_floor_display }}. Model comparison at this scale is noisy — a
  few-minute difference in MAE may not be statistically significant.
- **Non-stationarity:** Feeding patterns are changing rapidly as the baby
  grows (intervals lengthen, volumes increase). Models fitted to last week's
  data may not generalize to next week.
- **Breastfeeding volumes are estimated:** The {{ bf_heuristic }} heuristic
  is not measured intake. Models that use breastfeeding volume carry this
  uncertainty forward.

